How Big is Shapoorji Pallonji Group? | ET Now

Cyrus Mistry's sudden death has shocked everyone. Shapoorji Pallonji's business empire traces its roots back to 1865. Pallonji Mistry founded Littlewood Pallonji that year, a small construction company. At that time, Rs. 2000 was a huge amount for a project like paving Chowpatty. With a 18% stake in Tata Sons, the group is the largest individual shareholder of Tata Group, the gigantic conglomerate.
